The paper describes an algorithm for automated construction of a Bayesian network, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a probabilistic model and expert domain information suggests a focus on statistical inference (cs.SI) and data mining (cs.DM). The algorithm also involves a heuristic for minimizing the number of arcs added, which could be related to information theory (cs.IT).
